<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="J" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Jade1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Jade,</orth> subst. 1) a term of contempt or pity for a worthless, or wicked, or maltreated horse: <bibl n="shak. ven 391" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 391</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 707" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 707</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 51.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 51, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.277" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. III, 1, 277</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 2.1.269" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 1, 269</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.249" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 249</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.3.301" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls II, 3, 301</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.179" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 179</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 5.5.85" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 1, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 1, 7</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 1.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B I, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.178" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 178</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.5.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 5, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.26" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 7, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.2.46" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 3</bibl>.* <bibl n="shak. jc 4.2.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. IV, 2, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.253" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 253</bibl>. <cit><quote>--'s tricks:</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 145</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.5.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Alls IV, 5, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 1, 21</bibl>.<lb />2) a term of extreme contempt, when applied to persons, male as well as female: <cit><quote>no such j. as you,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.202" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 202</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I'ld play incessantly upon these --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.385" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 385</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I had as lief have my mistress a j.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.63" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 7, 63</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>